      • connect

        public boolean connect()
        Initiates a connection to the device with default user name, password and timeout. If connecting succeeds, the user is notified via the DataManSystem.OnConnectedListener. If an error occurs during connecting, the user is notified via the DataManSystem.OnConnectionErrorListener.
        Returns:
        true if the connection could be initiated (the state of the connection was ConnectionState.Disconnected, otherwise false.
        See Also:
        setTimeout(int), setOnConnectedListener(OnConnectedListener), setOnConnectionErrorListener(OnConnectionErrorListener)

      • connect

        public boolean connect(String userName,
                       String password)
        Initiates a connection to the device with the given user name and password and with the default timeout. If connecting succeeds, the user is notified via the DataManSystem.OnConnectedListener. If an error occurs during connecting, the user is notified via the DataManSystem.OnConnectionErrorListener.
        Parameters:
        userName - The user name to authenticate with the remote system.
        password - The password to authenticate with the remote system.
        Returns:
        true if the connection could be initiated (the state of the connection was ConnectionState.Disconnected, otherwise false.
        See Also:
        setTimeout(int), setOnConnectedListener(OnConnectedListener), setOnConnectionErrorListener(OnConnectionErrorListener)

      • disconnect

        public void disconnect()
        Initiates a disconnection from the device. If the DataManSystem.OnDisconnectedListener is set, it will be invoked after the device is disconnected.
        See Also:
        setOnDisconnectedListener(OnDisconnectedListener)

        public void sendCommand(String command,
                        byte[] data,
                        int timeout,
                        boolean expectBinaryResponse,
                        DataManSystem.OnResponseReceivedListener listener)
        Sends a command and the specified binary data to the connected device with the given timeout value. If a binary response is expected, it also can be specified. The user will be notified about the result in the DataManSystem.OnResponseReceivedListener.
        Parameters:
        command - The command to be send.
        data - Binary data to be send to the remote system.
        timeout - Timeout for the command.
        expectBinaryResponse - Value to indicate if we expect binary response.
        listener - The callback to be invoked when the answer to the command arrives.
        See Also:

      • sendCommandSync

        public DmccResponse sendCommandSync(String command,
                                    byte[] data,
                                    int timeout,
                                    boolean expectBinaryResponse)
                             throws InterruptedException,
                                    TimeoutException,
                                    DataManException,
                                    IOException
        Sends a command and the specified binary data to the connected device with the given timeout value. If a binary response is expected, it also can be specified. This method will block until the response from the Reader is received or the specified timeout has reached.
        Parameters:
        command - The command to be send.
        data - Binary data to be send to the remote system.
        timeout - Timeout for the command.
        expectBinaryResponse - Value to indicate if we expect binary response.
        Returns:
        DmccResponse Reader response for the sent command or null, if the command has failed
        Throws:
        InterruptedException - if the command sending is interrupted
        TimeoutException - if the command has timed out
        DataManException - if there was a command related issue
        IOException - if there was a communication issue

      • enableHeartbeat

        public void enableHeartbeat(int interval)
        Enables heartbeat and start sending heartbeat commands in every interval milliseconds. If a response to a heartbeat command is not received, the DataManSystem.OnHeartbeatResponseMissedListener is invoked if set.
        Parameters:
        interval - The interval (in milliseconds) between heartbeat commands.
        See Also:
        disableHeartbeat(), setOnHeartbeatResponseMissedListener(OnHeartbeatResponseMissedListener)
